CHOLERA - CONGO, DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Cholera - Congo, Dem.Rep. 980123230211
Date: Mon, 02 Feb 1998 09:56:57 -0800
From: Dr.James Chin, CDPC-mail
Source: WHO's Outbreak page - January 30, 1998

Cholera in Democratic Republic of the Congo
Cholera outbreaks have been reported in several health zones of the
Province of Katanga in the southeastern part of the country. The most
recent reports are from Kinkondja and Kenya-kamalondo. Kenya-kamalondo
health zone, which has a population of 170,000, experienced increased
activity in the last three months of 1997 when 327 cases were reported. The
weekly numbers have increased progressively since the first week of
January. In Kinkondja health zone (population 85,716), situated 100 km from
Bukama, the epidemic started around 10 January 1998 and since then at least
476 cases of which 84 were fatal have been reported by Médecins Sans
Frontières, Belgium. Most cases occurred in the week ending 25 January.
Cases had previously been reported in Kalémie and Bukama health zones and
recently also in the following zones: Kasenga (11 cases), Kilwa (20 cases),
Pweto (12 cases) and Kikula (51 cases).
